snippet.textDisplay:
I love you, your friends and your channel immensely. You are cute, funny and entertaining (here comes the "however" part): However, why do you insist on being referred to as "white guy" which draws attention to skin colour instead of language, which is the main, endearing reason your channel is so popular.
"American" doesn't work because most of the Chinese-speakers (at least in NYC) are probably American.

I'm certain you wouldn't refer to each ethnic group as a particular colour, so perhaps you can more aptly refer to your group as "Native English-speakers" or "Native anglophones"?
I realize it doesn't exactly roll off the tongue, but I think it's less objectionable than referring to people by the colour of their skin.
